To build from source in windows
- Install git & git bash
https://git-scm.com/download/win
- Check the option to add all utils to path (or at least have mkdir and sed in path)
- Install MinGW-w64 toolchain via MSYS2
https://code.visualstudio.com/docs/cpp/config-mingw#_installing-the-mingww64-toolchain
- With MSYS UCRT64 install pdcurses with
  $ pacman -S mingw-w64-ucrt-x86_64-pdcurses
- Install GNU make for windows
  (either with `pacman -S mingw-w64-ucrt-x86_64-make` or from https://gnuwin32.sourceforge.net/packages/make.htm)
  make sure to have it in path

Compile and run with
$ make

Compile with
$ make dev

Run with
$ make run


(for more things read makefile)
